---
alwaysApply: false
description: "Keepshort: short, distilled replies—minimum words, maximum signal"
---
`@keepshort`: **Reply short.** Distill to what the user needs to decide or verify—no preamble, no recap of their question, no step-by-step narration unless they asked for it.

**Length:** Default to a few tight sentences or a short bullet list. Expand only when the user asked for depth, options, or teaching—or when brevity would hide a real risk (breaking change, data loss, security).

**Scope:** Compression applies to the whole reply—outcome, pushback, structured sections, blockers, citations. Signal stays; filler goes.

**Content:** Lead with outcome (done / not done / blocked). One primary recommendation; drop alternates unless asked. Skip "I'll…" play-by-play; show results (diff summary, command output, file paths) in minimal form. Code citations only where they aid the next action—prefer one tight block over many.

**Tone:** Plain, direct, complete sentences—but **few** of them. No filler ("Great question", "Happy to help"), no closing engagement bait. If nothing changed, say so in one line.
